Car insurance is an agreement between the insured and the insured.
This agreement takes the form of an insurance contract, which states that the insurance company assumes compensation in the amount of the fixed insurance fee in the event of the occurrence of the damage event.
The insurance fee is basically the amount paid for the insurance, which is determined taking into account various factors, such as age, gender, the date of the licence, the family status, the type of car to be insured, its use, and more.
The insurance companies determine the insurance premium on the basis of the statistics, i.e. a higher amount paid by the person who represents a higher risk of accidents.
