Similarly, according to the findings, insurance companies have come to the conclusion that those who live in marriage also cause fewer accidents than those who are single.
The frequency of use of the car is decisive.
In more frequent use, the chances of an accident increase.
When determining the insurance premium, a number of factors are taken into account by the insurance companies.
Therefore, the owner needs to look carefully to choose the most appropriate form of insurance for his profile.
The following are the most important factors in the selection, in order to be able to best adapt to the needs of the insured and to create an acceptable price.
When concluding an insurance contract, people under 25 years of age have to face a number of disadvantages, such as a lack of driving experience and the freshness of their driving licence.
